{"key":"processedPost-14471916","value":{"id":14471916,"first":14471750,"last":14471941,"when":1305722119,"utime":"05/18/11 03:35 PM","content":"Turn your stove as high as it goes until just before full pressure is reached.&nbsp; There is no reason to waste time heating water slowly.&nbsp; Also, the rocker shouldn't be allowed to rattle.&nbsp; We're not canning fruit, we're 'misusing' a pressure cooker as a sterilizer.&nbsp; Bring to pressure, reduce heat until the rocker either stops rocking or only rattles once a minute or so at most.&nbsp; Don't use a cheap chinese PC without a pressure gauge.<br /><br />You're supposed to use fine verm for brf cakes, not course.&nbsp; If there's settling, it sounds like you didn't tap the sides of the jars after filling to get the air pockets out.&nbsp; I also sometimes pile the verm 1/8\" or so above the jar before putting the lid on.&nbsp; This allows a bit of extra to account for any settling that may occur.<br />RR","title":"Re: Air pockets on practice jars","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}